{"declarations":[{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/Contrapose.html#Mathlib.Tactic.Contrapose.contrapose!\"><span class=\"name\">Mathlib</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">Contrapose</span>.<span class=\"name\">contrapose!</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.ParserDescr\">Lean.ParserDescr</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"`contrapose` transforms the main goal into its contrapositive. If the goal has the form `⊢ P → Q`,\nthen `contrapose turns it into `⊢ ¬ Q → ¬ P`. If the goal has the form `⊢ P ↔ Q`, then `contrapose`\nturns it into `⊢ ¬ P ↔ ¬ Q`.\n\n* `contrapose h` on a goal of the form `h : P ⊢ Q` turns the goal into `h : ¬ Q ⊢ ¬ P`. This is\n  equivalent to `revert h; contrapose; intro h`.\n* `contrapose h with new_h` uses the name `new_h` for the introduced hypothesis. This is equivalent\n  to `revert h; contrapose; intro new_h`.\n* `contrapose!`, `contrapose! h` and `contrapose! h with new_h` push negation deeper into the goal\n  after contraposing (but before introducing the new hypothesis). See the `push_neg` tactic for more\n  details on the pushing algorithm.\n* `contrapose! (config := cfg)` controls the options for negation pushing. All options for\n  `Mathlib.Tactic.Push.Config` are supported:\n  * `contrapose! +distrib` rewrites `¬ (p ∧ q)` into `¬ p ∨ ¬ q` instead of `p → ¬ q`.\n\nExamples:\n```lean4\nvariables (P Q R : Prop)\n\nexample (H : ¬ Q → ¬ P) : P → Q := by\n  contrapose\n  exact H\n\nexample (H : ¬ P ↔ ¬ Q) : P ↔ Q := by\n  contrapose\n  exact H\n\nexample (H : ¬ Q → ¬ P) (h : P) : Q := by\n  contrapose h\n  exact H h\n\nexample (H : ¬ R → P → ¬ Q) : (P ∧ Q) → R := by\n  contrapose!\n  exact H\n\nexample (H : ¬ R → ¬ P ∨ ¬ Q) : (P ∧ Q) → R := by\n  contrapose! +distrib\n  exact H\n```\n","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Contrapose.html#Mathlib.Tactic.Contrapose.contrapose!","kind":"def","line":124,"name":"Mathlib.Tactic.Contrapose.contrapose!","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Tactic/Contrapose.lean#L124-L126"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/Contrapose.html#Mathlib.Tactic.Contrapose.contrapose\"><span class=\"name\">Mathlib</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">Contrapose</span>.<span class=\"name\">contrapose</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.ParserDescr\">Lean.ParserDescr</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"`contrapose` transforms the main goal into its contrapositive. If the goal has the form `⊢ P → Q`,\nthen `contrapose turns it into `⊢ ¬ Q → ¬ P`. If the goal has the form `⊢ P ↔ Q`, then `contrapose`\nturns it into `⊢ ¬ P ↔ ¬ Q`.\n\n* `contrapose h` on a goal of the form `h : P ⊢ Q` turns the goal into `h : ¬ Q ⊢ ¬ P`. This is\n  equivalent to `revert h; contrapose; intro h`.\n* `contrapose h with new_h` uses the name `new_h` for the introduced hypothesis. This is equivalent\n  to `revert h; contrapose; intro new_h`.\n* `contrapose!`, `contrapose! h` and `contrapose! h with new_h` push negation deeper into the goal\n  after contraposing (but before introducing the new hypothesis). See the `push_neg` tactic for more\n  details on the pushing algorithm.\n* `contrapose! (config := cfg)` controls the options for negation pushing. All options for\n  `Mathlib.Tactic.Push.Config` are supported:\n  * `contrapose! +distrib` rewrites `¬ (p ∧ q)` into `¬ p ∨ ¬ q` instead of `p → ¬ q`.\n\nExamples:\n```lean4\nvariables (P Q R : Prop)\n\nexample (H : ¬ Q → ¬ P) : P → Q := by\n  contrapose\n  exact H\n\nexample (H : ¬ P ↔ ¬ Q) : P ↔ Q := by\n  contrapose\n  exact H\n\nexample (H : ¬ Q → ¬ P) (h : P) : Q := by\n  contrapose h\n  exact H h\n\nexample (H : ¬ R → P → ¬ Q) : (P ∧ Q) → R := by\n  contrapose!\n  exact H\n\nexample (H : ¬ R → ¬ P ∨ ¬ Q) : (P ∧ Q) → R := by\n  contrapose! +distrib\n  exact H\n```\n","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Contrapose.html#Mathlib.Tactic.Contrapose.contrapose","kind":"def","line":46,"name":"Mathlib.Tactic.Contrapose.contrapose","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Tactic/Contrapose.lean#L46-L87"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/Contrapose.html#Mathlib.Tactic.Contrapose.contrapose_iff₄\"><span class=\"name\">Mathlib</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">Contrapose</span>.<span class=\"name\">contrapose_iff₄</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">p </span><span class=\"fn\">q</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">p</span> <a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Iff\">↔</a> <span class=\"fn\">q</span>) → (<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Not\">¬</a><span class=\"fn\">p</span> <a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Iff\">↔</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Not\">¬</a><span class=\"fn\">q</span>)</span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Contrapose.html#Mathlib.Tactic.Contrapose.contrapose_iff₄","kind":"theorem","line":44,"name":"Mathlib.Tactic.Contrapose.contrapose_iff₄","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Tactic/Contrapose.lean#L44-L44"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/Contrapose.html#Mathlib.Tactic.Contrapose.contrapose_iff₃\"><span class=\"name\">Mathlib</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">Contrapose</span>.<span class=\"name\">contrapose_iff₃</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">p </span><span class=\"fn\">q</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Not\">¬</a><span class=\"fn\">p</span> <a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Iff\">↔</a> <span class=\"fn\">q</span>) → (<span class=\"fn\">p</span> <a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Iff\">↔</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Not\">¬</a><span class=\"fn\">q</span>)</span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Contrapose.html#Mathlib.Tactic.Contrapose.contrapose_iff₃","kind":"theorem","line":43,"name":"Mathlib.Tactic.Contrapose.contrapose_iff₃","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Tactic/Contrapose.lean#L43-L43"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/Contrapose.html#Mathlib.Tactic.Contrapose.contrapose_iff₂\"><span class=\"name\">Mathlib</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">Contrapose</span>.<span class=\"name\">contrapose_iff₂</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">p </span><span class=\"fn\">q</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">p</span> <a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Iff\">↔</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Not\">¬</a><span class=\"fn\">q</span>) → (<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Not\">¬</a><span class=\"fn\">p</span> <a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Iff\">↔</a> <span class=\"fn\">q</span>)</span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Contrapose.html#Mathlib.Tactic.Contrapose.contrapose_iff₂","kind":"theorem","line":42,"name":"Mathlib.Tactic.Contrapose.contrapose_iff₂","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Tactic/Contrapose.lean#L42-L42"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/Contrapose.html#Mathlib.Tactic.Contrapose.contrapose_iff₁\"><span class=\"name\">Mathlib</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">Contrapose</span>.<span class=\"name\">contrapose_iff₁</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">p </span><span class=\"fn\">q</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Not\">¬</a><span class=\"fn\">p</span> <a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Iff\">↔</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Not\">¬</a><span class=\"fn\">q</span>) → (<span class=\"fn\">p</span> <a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Iff\">↔</a> <span class=\"fn\">q</span>)</span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Contrapose.html#Mathlib.Tactic.Contrapose.contrapose_iff₁","kind":"theorem","line":41,"name":"Mathlib.Tactic.Contrapose.contrapose_iff₁","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Tactic/Contrapose.lean#L41-L41"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/Contrapose.html#Mathlib.Tactic.Contrapose.contrapose₄\"><span class=\"name\">Mathlib</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">Contrapose</span>.<spa